Reasoning: The paper discusses the importance of preserving software resources on the Web for research purposes, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on preserving information on the Web. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the importance of software in research. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses identifying software mentions in scientific articles. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of software on research. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the need to preserve software resources over time.
